data.subject: ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor
data.question: What is the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node used for?
data.answer: The 3D Pose Editor node is used to set pose ControlNet in ComfyUI.

data.subject: ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor
data.question: What category does the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node belong to?
data.answer: The ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node belongs to the 'image/3D Pose Editor' category.

data.subject: Efficient Nodes KSampler Issue
data.question: What problem might occur when using Efficient KSampler with the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor?
data.answer: The KSampler output may not change if the pose editor is used, as there might be a caching issue.

data.subject: ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor
data.question: How can I add the workflow from the sample image to my ComfyUI?
data.answer: You can add the workflow from the sample image by downloading the PNG file and dropping it into your ComfyUI.

data.subject: ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor
data.question: What updates were made to the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor on 2024.01.04?
data.answer: On 2024.01.04, all the load methods were rewritten, and issues [#1], [#2], and [#4] were fixed. Credit is given to [@ltdrdata](https://github.com/ltdrdata) for their contributions.

data.subject: ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor
data.question: How can I fix the non-responsive ComfyUI interface?
data.answer: If your ComfyUI interface is not responding, you can try reloading your browser.
